      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/test-conditions-level2",
      "rationale": "Experimental test conditions (flow rates 2.5–6.0 L/min, rotational speeds 2000–3500 RPM, blood analogue fluid properties) are documented with calibrated measurement uncertainty. Temperature, fluid viscosity, and hematocrit are controlled and reported per ASTM F1841. Achieved level matches required level; conditions are representative of COU operating envelope.",
      "evidence": "https://uofa.net/synth/evidence/experimental-test-conditions-report"
    },
    {
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/output-comparison-level2",
      "rationale": "Quantitative comparison metrics (E_rel, validation uncertainty U_val) computed for velocity fields and NIH at all 5 operating points. Validation uncertainty estimated by combining experimental measurement uncertainty and numerical solution uncertainty per ASME V&V 20. All E_rel values fall within U_val bounds, confirming model adequacy. Achieved level 3 reflects multi-quantity, multi-operating-point comparison with formal uncertainty accounting.",
      "evidence": "https://uofa.net/synth/evidence/output-comparison-metrics-report"
    },
    {
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/qoi-relevance-level2",
      "rationale": "The primary quantity of interest — normalised index of hemolysis (NIH) — is the same quantity used in the regulatory submission and the clinical acceptance threshold. Secondary QoIs (wall shear stress, scalar residence time) are directly linked to the hemolysis power-law model inputs. QoI mapping from COU to simulation outputs is documented in the V&V plan.",
      "evidence": "https://uofa.net/synth/evidence/qoi-mapping-document"
    },
    {
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/validation-relevance-level2",
      "rationale": "Validation activities were performed on the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry — the same geometry as the COU device. Operating conditions span the full COU envelope. Blood analogue fluid (glycerin-water, viscosity matched) used in experiments. Achieved level 3 reflects direct geometric and operational correspondence between validation domain and COU, with documented similarity analysis.",
      "evidence": "https://uofa.net/synth/evidence/validation-relevance-similarity-analysis"
