    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-vv40-lead-assessor",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors have been assessed. Achieved credibility levels meet or exceed required levels for Model Risk Level 3 across every factor: Software QA (req 2, ach 3), Numerical code verification (req 2, ach 3), Discretization error (req 2, ach 3), Test conditions (req 2, ach 2), Output comparison (req 2, ach 3), Relevance of QoI (req 2, ach 2), Relevance of validation activities (req 2, ach 3), Numerical solver error (req 2, ach 2), Use error (req 2, ach 2), Model form (req 2, ach 3), Model inputs (req 2, ach 3), Test samples (req 2, ach 2), Equivalency of input parameters (req 2, ach 2). Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification (1000 samples) confirms that the 95th-percentile NIH prediction remains below the clinical acceptance threshold across all 5 operating points. Validation results for velocity fields and hemolysis index are all within validation uncertainty bounds. Provenance chain is complete from raw experimental data through simulation outputs to final comparison metrics. No credibility gaps remain. The CFD model is assessed as sufficiently credible for its intended use in the COU, and the submission is accepted.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
